---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home Loan - Starting @ 8.35% | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Home Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Home Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Turn your dream of owning a home into reality with our home loan offerings starting from just 8.35% p.a. Compare rates from India's top banks and NBFCs, and get the best deal tailored for you.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan: ₹5L - ₹10Cr</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-days"></i>
          <span>Tenure: Up to 30 Years</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 8.35% onwards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">

          <!-- Overview -->
          <h2>Home Loan Overview</h2>
          <p>A home loan is a secured loan offered by banks and financial institutions to help individuals purchase, construct, or renovate a residential property. The property itself serves as collateral, and the borrower repays the loan in Equated Monthly Instalments (EMIs) over a specified tenure.</p>
          <p>With TrueCred Loan Expert, you can compare home loan offers from 30+ leading lenders, check your eligibility in seconds, and apply online for the best rates — all from one platform. Whether you're a first-time buyer or looking to transfer your existing loan for a better rate, we've got you covered.</p>

          <!-- Info Grid -->
          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.35%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹10 Crore</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">30 Yrs</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Tenure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Rate Table -->
          <h3>Home Loan Interest Rates 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Lender</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>SBI</strong></td>
                <td>8.50% onwards</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
                <td>Up to 0.35%</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>HDFC</strong></td>
                <td>8.60% onwards</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>ICICI Bank</strong></td>
                <td>8.75% onwards</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>LIC HFL</strong></td>
                <td>8.35% onwards</td>
                <td>30 Years</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>PNB Housing</strong></td>
                <td>8.65% onwards</td>
                <td>25 Years</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <!-- Types of Home Loans -->
          <h3>Types of Home Loans</h3>
          <div class="info-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);">
            <div class="info-box">
              <i class="fas fa-house-chimney" style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px;"></i>
              <span class="info-value" style="font-size: 1rem;">Home Purchase</span>
              <span class="info-label">Buy a new or resale property</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <i class="fas fa-helmet-safety" style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px;"></i>
              <span class="info-value" style="font-size: 1rem;">Construction</span>
              <span class="info-label">Build your dream house</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <i class="fas fa-paint-roller" style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px;"></i>
              <span class="info-value" style="font-size: 1rem;">Renovation</span>
              <span class="info-label">Upgrade your existing home</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <i class="fas fa-map-location-dot" style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px;"></i>
              <span class="info-value" style="font-size: 1rem;">Plot Loan</span>
              <span class="info-label">Purchase a residential plot</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <i class="fas fa-plane-departure" style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px;"></i>
              <span class="info-value" style="font-size: 1rem;">NRI Home Loan</span>
              <span class="info-label">For non-resident Indians</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <i class="fas fa-arrow-right-arrow-left" style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px;"></i>
              <span class="info-value" style="font-size: 1rem;">Balance Transfer</span>
              <span class="info-label">Switch to a lower rate</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Eligibility -->
          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <p>Meeting the following criteria improves your chances of home loan approval:</p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Indian citizen or NRI aged between 21 and 65 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Salaried individuals with minimum 2 years of work experience</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Self-employed professionals with at least 3 years of business vintage</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum monthly income of ₹25,000 (varies by lender)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 700 or above for the best interest rates</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Clear repayment track record with no active defaults</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Property must be legally approved and free from encumbrances</li>
          </ul>

          <!-- How to Apply -->
          <h3>How to Apply for a Home Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Check Eligibility</h4>
              <p>Use our eligibility calculator to know how much loan you qualify for.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Compare Offers</h4>
              <p>Compare interest rates, tenure and processing fees from 30+ lenders.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Submit Application</h4>
              <p>Fill in your details and upload the required documents online.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Get Disbursement</h4>
              <p>After verification and property valuation, loan is disbursed to your account.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Documents Required -->
          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-lines"></i> Identity proof — Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Passport, Voter ID</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-lines"></i> Address proof — Utility bill, Aadhaar Card, Rental Agreement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-lines"></i> Income proof — Salary slips (last 3 months), Form 16, ITR for 2 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-lines"></i> Bank statements for the last 6 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-lines"></i> Property documents — Sale deed, title deed, approved building plan</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-lines"></i> Builder-buyer agreement or allotment letter</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-lines"></i> Passport-size photographs</li>
          </ul>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">

          <!-- Apply Form -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-paper-plane" style="color: var(--primary); margin-right: 8px;"></i> Apply for Home Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Property Value</option>
                  <option value="below-25l">Below ₹25 Lakh</option>
                  <option value="25l-50l">₹25 Lakh - ₹50 Lakh</option>
                  <option value="50l-1cr">₹50 Lakh - ₹1 Crore</option>
                  <option value="1cr-3cr">₹1 Crore - ₹3 Crore</option>
                  <option value="3cr-5cr">₹3 Crore - ₹5 Crore</option>
                  <option value="above-5cr">Above ₹5 Crore</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>City</option>
                  <option value="mumbai">Mumbai</option>
                  <option value="delhi">Delhi NCR</option>
                  <option value="bangalore">Bangalore</option>
                  <option value="hyderabad">Hyderabad</option>
                  <option value="chennai">Chennai</option>
                  <option value="pune">Pune</option>
                  <option value="kolkata">Kolkata</option>
                  <option value="ahmedabad">Ahmedabad</option>
                  <option value="other">Other</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
              <p class="form-disclaimer">
                <i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Your data is 100% safe & secure
              </p>
            </form>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Links -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link" style="color: var(--primary); margin-right: 8px;"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="#"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="#"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan Eligibility Calculator</a>
              <a href="#"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan Balance Transfer</a>
              <a href="#"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan Prepayment</a>
              <a href="#"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Renovation Loan</a>
              <a href="#"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> NRI Home Loan</a>
              <a href="#"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Plot Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Personal Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about home loans, answered.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the minimum CIBIL score required for a home loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Most banks and NBFCs require a minimum CIBIL score of 700 to approve a home loan. However, some lenders may consider applicants with scores as low as 650, though at higher interest rates. A score of 750+ typically qualifies you for the best rates and faster processing.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How much home loan can I get based on my salary?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              As a general rule, most lenders offer a home loan amount that is 50 to 60 times your monthly salary. For example, if your salary is ₹50,000 per month, you may be eligible for a loan of ₹25 Lakh to ₹30 Lakh. The exact amount depends on your existing obligations, credit score, age, and the lender's internal policies.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get a home loan with zero down payment?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              No, as per RBI guidelines, banks can finance up to 75-90% of the property value depending on the loan amount. You are required to pay the remaining 10-25% as a down payment from your own funds. For loans up to ₹30 Lakh, the LTV ratio can be up to 90%, while for higher amounts it reduces to 75-80%.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What are the tax benefits on a home loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Home loan borrowers can claim tax deductions under multiple sections of the Income Tax Act. Under Section 80C, you can claim up to ₹1.5 Lakh on the principal repayment. Under Section 24(b), up to ₹2 Lakh can be claimed on interest paid for a self-occupied property. First-time home buyers can also claim an additional deduction of ₹1.5 Lakh under Section 80EEA for affordable housing.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I prepay my home loan without penalty?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              If your home loan carries a floating interest rate, there is no prepayment penalty as per RBI guidelines. You can make partial or full prepayments at any time. For fixed-rate home loans, some lenders may charge a prepayment penalty of 2-3% on the outstanding principal. It's advisable to check the terms with your lender before making prepayments.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-bottom: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Ready to Own Your Dream Home?</h3>
          <p>Get personalized home loan offers from India's top banks at competitive rates. Apply in minutes!</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
